text.tspan: Changes in energy use vs. changes in GDP, Sweden
Consumption-based (trade-adjusted) energy use measures domestic energy use minus energy used to produce
exported goods, plus energy used to produce imported goods.
Data source: Energy data is calculated by Viktoras Kulionis, based on the EXIOBASE v3.8.2 database; GDP data from the World Bank
Note: GDP is measured in 2017 constant international-$ which adjusts for inflation and cross-country price differences.
